      "frames": [
        {
          "id": "chapter-2-arrival",
          "title": "The Price of Entry",
          "paragraphs": [
            "The murder ledger is sealed by the library's balance, so Oriel offers the memory of her mother's farewell at the station. The page opens to reveal that Alis was killed after tracing stolen research to a celebrated university chair.",
            "The surrendered memory takes root as The Mnemonic Briar, tangling true images with comforting inventions. Oriel cuts a path by recording what she can still prove, but leaves unable to recall why her mother looked proud."
          ],
          "semanticLabel": "A glowing memory grows into thorned roots around Oriel and an open forbidden ledger.",
          "actionLabel": "Carry out the clue"
        }
      ]
    },
