          "id": "chapter-5-arrival",
          "title": "What We Forgot Together",
          "paragraphs": [
            "A locked testimony demands a memory neither investigator owns alone, and Oriel and Matias sacrifice the night their rivalry became friendship. They emerge with proof that Alis named her killer, yet with every affectionate reason to distrust one another restored to suspicion.",
            "The lost night ignites into The Cinder Thesis, which burns their shared notes whenever either acts alone. By following the habits their former selves left in the margins, Oriel and Matias quench it together and choose trust as a present action rather than a recovered feeling."
          ],
          "semanticLabel": "Oriel and Matias join separated notes across a burning lecture hall while a figure of ember and ash rises.",
          "actionLabel": "Choose trust again"
        }
      ]
