          "id": "chapter-6-arrival",
          "title": "The Prestige of Silence",
          "paragraphs": [
            "Alis's murder file opens onto a century of dissent erased, discoveries reassigned, and patrons protected by ceremonial acclaim. Curator Vey argues that the bargains prevented unrest, while Oriel sees how carefully the cost was forced upon people with the least protection.",
            "The archive's authorship machine becomes The Citation Engine, stamping stolen names beneath portraits of university heroes. Oriel and Matias reverse its proof chain until every prestigious claim points back to the silenced scholar who made it."
          ],
          "semanticLabel": "A brass authorship machine stamps false citations beneath grand portraits while Oriel reverses its gears.",
          "actionLabel": "Trace every stolen name"
        }
      ]
    },
