          "title": "Witnesses Beyond the Stacks",
          "paragraphs": [
            "Curator Vey seals every exit and offers Oriel one final private audience, insisting that uncontrolled truth will punish innocent people along with the guilty. Instead, the investigators divide Alis's testimony among printers, street teachers, former borrowers, and the living shadows of other victims.",
            "The Tenure Wraith hunts each messenger by wearing the faces of authorities they once trusted. Alis's Shadow teaches the witnesses to compare what they remember, and their overlapping accounts leave the specter no solitary mind to haunt."
          ],
          "semanticLabel": "A chain of witnesses passes luminous pages beyond the stacks while an academic specter changes faces behind them.",
          "actionLabel": "Send the witnesses outward"
        }
      ]
    },
