          "id": "chapter-8-arrival",
          "title": "The Open Catalog",
          "paragraphs": [
            "At the master catalog, Vey offers to reveal Alis's final minute in exchange for Oriel's reason for seeking justice. Oriel refuses the bargain and links the catalog to thousands of readers above, accepting uncertainty so the evidence can survive outside any chosen keeper.",
            "The library gathers its doctrine of perfect control into The Quiet Constellation, a sky of cold index lights that blanks every unapproved connection. Oriel lets readers draw their own lines between the facts, breaking the pattern and opening every shelf at once."
          ],
          "semanticLabel": "Thousands of catalog lights form a false constellation above Oriel as open pages stream toward the city.",
          "actionLabel": "Open the catalog"
        }
      ]
