          "id": "a-thousand-copies",
          "title": "Truth in a Thousand Hands",
          "paragraphs": [
            "By morning, Alis's testimony and the stolen discoveries cover printshop walls, classroom slates, and kitchen tables across the city. No curator can reclaim a truth that neighbors now keep for one another.",
            "The university begins answering for the murder and the thefts behind it. The reckoning is untidy, but the people once treated as footnotes finally speak under their own names."
          ],
          "semanticLabel": "Citizens read copied catalog pages across a rain-washed square as the university doors stand open.",
          "actionLabel": "See what remains"
        },
        {
          "id": "the-memory-we-make",
          "title": "The Memory We Make",
          "paragraphs": [
            "Oriel cannot recover her mother's farewell or the lost beginning of her friendship with Matias. She can choose what comes next, and together they record every future loan, cost, and consent in an open ledger.",
            "Alis's Shadow settles beside her own credited work, no longer the collection's only witness. Beneath the city, the Ninth Library is still dangerous, but its doors now open under many watchful eyes."
          ],
          "semanticLabel": "Oriel, Matias, and Alis's peaceful shadow write in an open ledger beneath newly unlocked library doors.",
          "actionLabel": "Return to the map",
